extends lib/base.pug

append head
  style: include lib/bg-dark.css
  style: include heresies.css

  - const PAGE_ID='heresies'

mixin belief(title)
  .card
    h2= title

mixin heresy(title, doctrine, proof_texts, origin, problems)
  .card
    h2!= title
    p #[strong False doctrine:] #{doctrine}
    if origin
      p #[strong Origin:] #{origin}
    if attributes.aka
      p #[strong Also known as:] #{attributes.aka}
    // if attributes.deception
    //   p #[strong Level of Deception:] #{attributes.deception}
    .tooltip-anchor
      strong.tooltip.help Proof-texts:
        span.tooltiptext These Scripture verses are the most common ones used to promote this false doctrine.
      +refs(proof_texts)
    if problems
      p #[strong Problems:] #{problems}
    .defense.tooltip-anchor
      h3 ~ Rebuttal ~
      block

append main
  .card.dark
    h1 Heresies
    p.tooltip-anchor
      | Friends, let us be vigilant, for the devil came to Jesus abusing Scripture
      +see('Mat.4:6', 'see'): |  and has been doing the same for thousands of years. The apostle Peter warns us how some of Paul's writings are hard to understand and will be twisted by the unlearned
      +see('2-Pet.3:15-16', 'see'): |. Jesus warns us to beware of false prophets and false doctrines
      +see('Mat.7:15-20, 16:6,12', 'see'): |.
    .verses
      +verse('1-Tim.4:1,2')(seeAlso='2-Cor.11:3-4, 11:13-15'): :markdown-it Now the Spirit expressly says that in latter times some will depart from the faith, giving heed to deceiving spirits and *doctrines of demons*, speaking lies in hypocrisy, having their own conscience seared with a hot iron,
      +verse('2-Pet.2:1')(seeAlso='Acts 20:29-31'): :markdown-it But there were also false prophets among the people, even as there will be *false teachers* among you, who will secretly bring in *destructive heresies*, even denying the Lord who bought them, and bring on themselves swift destruction.
      +verse('Jude 1:3')(seeAlso='Jude 1:4; Eph.5:11'): :markdown-it Beloved, while I was very diligent to write to you concerning our common salvation, I found it necessary to write to you exhorting you to contend earnestly for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.
      +verse('2-Tim.4:3-4'): :markdown-it For the time will come when they will not endure sound doctrine, but according to their *own desires*, because they have itching ears, they will heap up for themselves teachers; and they will turn their ears away from the truth, and be *turned aside to fables*.
    p.mb-0 Neither the prophets, nor the Lord Jesus, nor His apostles taught any of the doctrines found below.
  .cards.dark
    +heresy(
      'Penal Substitution Atonement (PSA)',
      'Jesus paid the penalty for our past, present and future sins. The wrath of God was poured out and satisfied as the Father punished the Son so we can go free.',
      'Is.53:4,6,10; Mat.27:46; Rom.3:25; Col.2:14; 1-John 2:2, 4:10',
      '(Anselm, Aquinas), Luther, Calvin',
      'Maligns God\'s character and logically leads to double jeopardy or universalism, which can lead to Calvinism\'s limited atonement. Also, this does not fix the believer\'s relationship with God, only their legal standing.')(deception='High')
      p.tooltip-anchor In
        +refs('Mat.18:23-27; Luke 7:41,42', 'and'): |the unpayable debt is #[em forgiven], not paid off. In
        +refs('Mark 10:45; 1-Tim.2:6', 'and'): |Jesus is our #[em ransom] i.e. our Passover lamb, a #[em sin offering] to lead us to repentance.
      p Jesus is quoting
        +refs('Psa.22:1'): |on the cross.
        | The sacrificial animals in Leviticus were not being punished.
        | The Septuagint version of Isaiah 53:10 reads very differently to the Masoretic.
    +heresy(
      'Justification by Faith Alone',
      'We are justified by faith alone, not by anything we do (our works).',
      'John 6:29; Rom.3:28, 10:9; Eph.2:8-9',
      'Luther',
      'Deceives the believer into thinking what they do plays no role in their salvation (monergism). Therefore there is little or no incentive for good works or obedience to God. For example, baptism is not required for salvation.')(aka='Sola Fide')
      p.tooltip-anchor This doctrine contradicts
        +refs('James 2:14-26'): |which says we are justified by (good) works (of faith and obedience), and that faith (alone) without works is dead.
        +refs('Rom.3:24, 5:9; Titus 3:7', 'and'): |says we are also justified by grace and the blood.
      p.tooltip-anchor
        +refs('Mark 16:16; 1-Pet.3:21'): |says baptism is a necessary part of salvation.
      p We must have good works (of faithful obedience) to enter the kingdom of heaven:
        +refs('Rom.2:5-10; Luke 13:24-27; Gal.6:7-10; Rev.20:12,13')
        |. We are not earning salvation, for it is a gift from God, with conditions.
    +heresy(
      'Original Sin',
      'Everyone is born with a sinful nature inherited from Adam, with damnable guilt at birth.',
      'Psa.51:5; John 3:6; Rom.5:12; Eph.2:3',
      'Augustine (influcenced by Gnosticism)',
      'Deceives the believer into thinking God made them a certain way which is impossible to repent of. Allows sinners to blame God, not themselves, for their sins, therefore God is unjust to judge them. Also leads to the unbiblical practice of infant baptism.')
      p.tooltip-anchor God sees little children as innocent:
        +refs('Deut.1:39; Mat.18:2-5; Luke 18:15-17; Rom.9:11')
      p.tooltip-anchor God will not hold us accountable for Adam's sin, only our own:
        +refs('Deut.24:16; Eze.18:19-20')
      p Gnostics mis-interpreted Ephesians 2:3 as concerning damnation by nature rather than personal sins. Gnosticism teaches all flesh is created evil.
      // 'Isaiah 7:15; Jer.19:4; John 9:41')
    +heresy(
      'Imputed Righteousness',
      'Jesus\' righteousness is transferred onto us, and our sins are transferred onto Jesus, in a divine exchange.',
      'Is.64:6; Rom.4:6; 1-Cor.1:30; 2-Cor.5:21',
      'Luther, Calvin',
      'Abuses Isaiah 64:6, taking it out of context to deceive the believer into thinking they cannot become righteous before God. Therefore God must give us His righteousness apart from our works (monergism). Changes our legal status with God.')(aka='Double Imputation')
      p.tooltip-anchor
        +refs('1-John 3:7,8'): |says whoever #[em practices] righteousness is righteous.
      p.tooltip-anchor
        +refs('Gal.5:19-21'): |says whoever does not #[em practice] righteousness cannot inherit the kingdom of God.
      p
        +refs('Rev.19:8'): |says the white robe is the righteous #[em acts] of the saints.
    +heresy(
      'Eternal security',
      'You cannot be lost once you\'re saved.',
      'John 6:37; Rom.8:38,39; Php.1:6',
      '',
      'Deceives the believer into thinking they are saved when really they are not, that they can live in sin and enter the kingdom.')(aka='Once Saved Always Saved')
      p The Bible gives warning after warning
      +refs('Mat.24:13; Heb.6:4-6, 10:26-31; 2-Pet.2:20-22')
    .card
      h2 Other Heresies
      :markdown-it
